<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In Macau, adults are active only in late spring and range in total length 22-27 mm and 6-9 mm in maximum width. They are mainly nocturnal and readily attracted to artificial lights. In nearby Hong Kong, larvae utilise a wide variety of food plants, including 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fabaceae" genus="Adenanthera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Adenanthera miscrosperma" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="miscrosperma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Adenanthera miscrosperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rutaceae" genus="Citrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Citrus reticulata" order="Rutales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="reticulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Citrus reticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Meliaceae" genus="Melia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Melia azedarach" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="azedarach">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Melia azedarach</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Aves" family="Sulidae" genus="Morus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Morus alba" order="Ciconiiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Morus alba</emphasis>
